#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Repeated participant-grouped H0 Alpha-Pi classification for IBD vs non-IBD.

This is the publication/GitHub-oriented repeated-CV implementation of the
train-only adaptive-bin H0 Alpha-Pi classifier.

Primary design
--------------
* Task: IBD (UC + CD) versus non-IBD.
* Outer evaluation: an existing 20 x 5 participant-grouped split manifest is
  loaded directly. The default is the manifest generated by the repeated Ricci
  analysis, so H0 and Ricci are evaluated on exactly the same held-out samples
  and participants.
* Inner model selection in every outer fold:
    1. split outer-training participants once into grouped inner-train and
       validation subsets (default: one fold from grouped 5-fold CV);
    2. for each adaptive percentile step, construct H0 interval boundaries
       from inner-train death values only;
    3. train Alpha-Pi on inner-train and select the best epoch on validation;
    4. select the percentile step by validation balanced accuracy, then macro
       F1, logit ROC-AUC, and finally fewer intervals.
* Final outer-fold model:
    1. rebuild adaptive boundaries from all outer-training death values using
       the selected percentile step;
    2. initialize a fresh model;
    3. train on all outer-training samples for the selected number of epochs;
    4. evaluate exactly once on the untouched outer-test fold.
* Primary prediction rule: CE/logit head. Nearest-centroid outputs are saved as
  diagnostics only.
* Primary performance distribution: 20 pooled out-of-fold repetition results.
  The 100 fold scores are retained for diagnostics and stability analysis, but
  are not treated as 100 independent estimates.

Interpretation outputs
----------------------
For every final outer-fold model this script saves:
* raw and normalized alpha curves;
* the binary logit-head contrast;
* the signed single-death influence curve g(d), which directly measures how an
  H0 death at scale d changes the IBD-vs-non-IBD logit contrast;
* held-out z features and per-interval logit contributions;
* all model parameters, adaptive bounds, training history and test predictions.

Resume behavior
---------------
Candidate fits and completed outer folds are written atomically. Re-running the
same command resumes from completed artifacts after checking the saved run
configuration and input fingerprints.
"""

